  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2022",
  "title": "<Highlight /> drops part of a string",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nbug\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nUsing `<Highlight />` parts of a match *after* the highlighted tag will be dropped. Could be related to having a `-` directly after the last word.\r\n\r\nCan be seen on <https://yarnpkg.com/en/packages?q=react-instant>, where the first three results are actually different packages (relatively `react-instantsearch`, `react-instantsearch-theme-algolia` and `react-instantsearch-vl`).\r\n\r\nThe whole string will show up when a query that ends at the dash is given (e.g. <https://yarnpkg.com/en/packages?q=react-instantsearch>)\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nThe complete string to be visible.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\n\r\nAll browsers\r\n\r\n**What project are you opening an issue for?**\r\n- react-instantsearch\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n",
